6. Better Approach (Prefix Sum)

Idea

Instead of counting ones and zeros repeatedly,

compute prefix sums.

Convert

1 → +1
0 → -1

For every substring

sum = prefix[j+1] - prefix[i]

Check whether it is positive.

This removes repeated counting.


---

Algorithm

Create prefix sum array.

For every pair (i,j)

        sum = prefix[j+1]-prefix[i]

        if sum > 0

              answer++


---

Code

class Solution:
    def countSubstring(self, s):

        n = len(s)

        prefix = [0] * (n + 1)

        for i in range(n):

            val = 1 if s[i] == '1' else -1

            prefix[i + 1] = prefix[i] + val

        ans = 0

        for i in range(n):
            for j in range(i, n):

                if prefix[j + 1] - prefix[i] > 0:
                    ans += 1

        return ans


---

Time Complexity

O(n²)


